Set free-space thresholds for Main. When **remaining free space** falls to or below a threshold, that Free bar goes **yellow** (warning) or **red** (critical). **None** leaves a level unused. If both levels are set, the **lower free-space amount** is critical and the **higher** is warning. Units can be T, G, etc. (for example `8T` or `500G`).

Highlight style is chosen **separately** for the array and for each pool. **Solid** is the default (recolor the free bar). **Outline** keeps Unraid’s fill and draws a border instead.

_(Outline — pulse on warning/critical?)_:
: <select name="outline_pulse" id="outline_pulse">
  <?=mk_option($outline_pulse, "no", _("No (static outline)"))?>
  <?=mk_option($outline_pulse, "yes", _("Yes (pulsing outline)"))?>
  </select>

<blockquote class="inline_help">
Only applies when a target uses <strong>Outline</strong> style. Default is static. Pulse can make yellow/red easier to notice.
</blockquote>

_(Outline — green border when free space is OK?)_:
: <select name="outline_show_ok" id="outline_show_ok">
  <?=mk_option($outline_show_ok, "no", _("No"))?>
  <?=mk_option($outline_show_ok, "yes", _("Yes — green outline when above thresholds"))?>
  </select>

<blockquote class="inline_help">
Only for <strong>Outline</strong> style. When free space is still healthy (above your thresholds), draw a <strong>static green</strong> outline so you can see “still enough free space” at a glance. Off by default. Does nothing in Solid mode.
</blockquote>

